<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Kate Middleton and Prince William helped to knead dough as they visited Brick Lane's famous Beigel Bake today to highlight how communities have coped during Covid-19. </p>

<p>The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge, both 38, who were living at their Norfolk home of Anmer Hall during the lockdown but are believed to be back at their London base of Kensington Palace, travelled to London Bridge and Whitechapel for several visits throughout the day.</p>

<p>The couple, who have not appeared together in public since July, appeared relaxed during the outing, and were said to be keen to shine a light on individuals and businesses who have gone above and beyond to help others during this extraordinary time. </p>

<p>Kate recycled her Beulah London red midi dress for the appearance in the capital, pairing the look with a pair of nude heels and her floral mask. </p>

